@Node "Spielregeln" "How to Play"

This part of the docs was written by Matthew O'Neill, mash@dingnet.demon.co.uk

The object of the game is to work out the computers 4 chosen symbols

these are either:

disk
network
ram
volume
harddisk
drawer

if this is your first game, then click on each symbol and choose one at random.
Now click on the guess button. You should see something pop up at the top. it will
tell you that this is the first try, then it tells you which symbols you chose,
and next it will give you an evaluation.

@{b}what the hell do the dots mean?!@{ub}

right, if you get 1 black dot, then this means one of your choices is completely
correct, so if you get 2 black dots then you will know that you have 2 correct
and so on. the only thing is though, it will not tell you which symbol is correct
(:P)

now if you get a white dot then you are half right. a white dot means you have
the correct symbol, but it is in the wrong place (so put it somewhere else!)

from these dots you should be able to work out the answer. but beware, you only
get 8 guesses at what it could be.

good luck!

note: each symbol can be used more than once!

@{b}more help@{ub}

Q: I have 4 white dots!, what now?

A: this means that you have all the correct symbols you need, the only problem is
that they are all in the wrong places! have a look at your previous attempts, if
you had a black dot somewhere, then this means that you did have a symbol in the
right, place, but you have since moved it. compare your current symbols with
that one and see which symbols are the same, it @{b}must@{ub} have been one of them.

